name: Cavs
summary: The Cleveland Cavaliers will face the Orlando Magic in the opening weekend of the NBA playoffs. The series will begin with Game 1 in Cleveland on Saturday, April 15th. Game 2 will be played on Monday, April 17th, also in Cleveland. The series will then move to Orlando for Games 3 and 4 on Wednesday, April 19th and Friday, April 21st. If necessary, Game 5 will be played back in Cleveland on Sunday, April 23rd, and Game 6 will be played in Orlando on Tuesday, April 25th. A potential Game 7 would be played back in Cleveland on Thursday, April 27th.

summary: The United States House of Representatives has recently voted to consider a potential ban on the popular social media app TikTok. This move follows concerns about national security and data privacy, as TikTok is owned by the Chinese company ByteDance. Despite the vote, experts believe that an outright ban of the app is unlikely in the near future. The bill faces further debate in Congress and would require support from the Senate and the President's signature to become law. Meanwhile, TikTok users and businesses can expect the app to continue operating for the time being.
